# S2A Component Audit

Audit an S2A Figma component page for normalization issues. Flag, do not fix.

## What to audit

**Property panel order** — must be: Variants → Booleans → Instance Swaps → Text → Nested props

**Variant value casing** — all values must be lowercase-kebab: `default`, `hover`, `on-light`, `sm`, `md`

**Layer naming** — no unnamed layers (`Frame 1`, `Group 47`, `Rectangle 3`). Root frame must be `.root`. Optional elements dot-prefixed kebab-case.

**Token binding** — no hex values, no raw px in fills/strokes. Every fill must reference an S2A variable.

**Documentation completeness** — check if a doc sheet exists. Flag if missing.

**Unused properties** — flag any boolean or instance swap that is never toggled across variants.

## Output format
Return a markdown table per component set:
| Issue | Property/Layer | Current | Expected | Severity |
```
High   = blocks engineering handoff
Medium = naming/casing inconsistency
Low    = documentation gap
```
